INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {'script': "Welcome, esteemed scholars and curious adventurers, to the heart of academic excellence, our magnificent University Library! I'm absolutely delighted to be your guide today, leading you on a walking tour of this impressive campus. As we begin, I invite you to take a moment and soak in the vibrant atmosphere. We'll be exploring five key areas that truly define our commitment to learning and discovery.\n\nOur first stop, and indeed the anchor of our entire campus, is right here at the grand entrance of the Main Research Building. Just look up and around you! This impressive structure, with its stately architecture and iconic clock tower, is far more than just a building; it's the very nerve center of our university's intellectual pursuits. Within these walls, countless volumes of knowledge are meticulously curated, groundbreaking research is conducted, and a dynamic community of learners thrives. It houses our extensive collection, state-of-the-art study spaces, and various specialized departments. The glass-covered walkways you see are not just beautiful architectural features, but also practical connections, allowing for seamless movement and natural light throughout the complex. It truly embodies the spirit of scholarly endeavor.\n\nNow, let's embark on a gentle stroll. If you'll follow me, we'll head just to our right, moving in a graceful clockwise direction around our beautiful grounds. Our next destination is a truly unique architectural gem, a place of immense significance for our academic community: The Thesis Repository. As we approach this striking golden hexagonal structure, you can immediately feel its special aura. This isn't just an eye-catching design; it’s a deliberate choice, symbolizing the precious and monumental contributions housed within. Imagine, every master's thesis, every doctoral dissertation, every capstone project that has shaped our university's legacy, finds its home here. It’s a living archive, a testament to the dedication and intellectual rigor of generations of scholars. The golden hue reflects not only the sun but also the invaluable knowledge contained within, shining brightly as a beacon of academic achievement.\n\nFrom the golden glow of The Thesis Repository, we’ll continue our clockwise journey, heading southward. As we turn, a tranquil scene will unfold before us: the serene Reflection Pond. This beautiful expanse of water, with its elegant central fountain, offers a peaceful contrast to the academic bustle. It’s more than just an aesthetic feature; it serves as a calming oasis, a place for quiet contemplation and reflection. Students and faculty alike often gather here, finding inspiration in its still waters, or simply taking a moment to unwind between studies. The gentle ripples from the fountain create a soothing ambiance, making it a beloved spot for personal reflection and a quiet break from intense research.\n\nOur journey now takes us westward from the Reflection Pond, leading us to an area designed specifically for focused, outdoor learning and thought: the Quiet Study Garden. As we step into this beautifully manicured green space, you’ll notice the deliberate arrangement of hedges and trees, creating secluded nooks and open lawns. This garden is a sanctuary for those seeking a peaceful environment away from the conventional study halls. It’s perfect for reading, thoughtful discussion, or simply enjoying the natural surroundings while engaging with academic materials. We believe that nature provides a powerful complement to intellectual work, and this garden is a living testament to that philosophy, offering a refreshing perspective and an inspiring backdrop for deep thought.\n\nFinally, as we complete our loop and find ourselves drawing closer to our starting point, we arrive at the expansive Central Quadrangle Plaza. This magnificent paved area, stretching out before the Main Research Building, is truly the social and communal heart of our campus. It's where students gather between classes, where lively discussions spill out from the lecture halls, and where important university events often take place. It connects all the major buildings, serving as a dynamic crossroads and a vibrant gathering space. From formal ceremonies to casual meetings, this plaza buzzes with the energy of academic life, fostering connections and a strong sense of community. It's the perfect place to witness the pulse of our university.\n\nThank you so much for joining me on this tour of our remarkable University Library campus. I hope you've enjoyed discovering these unique spaces as much as I've enjoyed sharing them with you. Please feel free to explore further at your leisure, and I wish you a wonderful rest of your visit!", 'labels': [{'number': 1, 'location_name': 'Main Research Building', 'ymin': 153.0, 'xmin': 350.0, 'ymax': 305.0, 'xmax': 602.0, 'x': None, 'y': None, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'The central entrance section of the main grey building, featuring a prominent clock tower and glass canopy.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 2, 'location_name': 'The Thesis Repository', 'ymin': 442.0, 'xmin': 509.0, 'ymax': 710.0, 'xmax': 820.0, 'x': None, 'y': None, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'The distinctive golden octagonal building with a prominent central roof structure.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 3, 'location_name': 'Reflection Pond', 'ymin': 704.0, 'xmin': 442.0, 'ymax': 843.0, 'xmax': 686.0, 'x': None, 'y': None, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'The large rectangular blue water body with a central fountain.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 4, 'location_name': 'Quiet Study Garden', 'ymin': 546.0, 'xmin': 337.0, 'ymax': 681.0, 'xmax': 476.0, 'x': None, 'y': None, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'A distinct, manicured rectangular green lawn area bordered by hedges, designed for quiet contemplation.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 5, 'location_name': 'Central Quadrangle Plaza', 'ymin': 290.0, 'xmin': 270.0, 'ymax': 680.0, 'xmax': 720.0, 'x': None, 'y': None, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'The expansive central paved area connecting major buildings and gardens, serving as a primary pedestrian and gathering space.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}]}
