INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {"script":"Welcome, adventurers, to an exclusive behind-the-scenes look at one of the world's most innovative high-tech international airport terminals! I'm thrilled to be your guide today as we explore the cutting-edge design and sustainable features that make this facility truly remarkable. We're about to embark on a fascinating walking tour, so get ready to discover the heart of modern air travel. Our journey begins here, with Stop Number One: the magnificent Main Terminal Building A. As you can see, this vast grey structure is the central hub of our airport, a beacon of efficiency and architectural prowess. Notice its expansive rooftop, ingeniously designed to house a significant array of solar panels, capturing clean energy to power much of our operations. The building's sleek, modular design hints at the advanced technology housed within, ensuring a seamless experience for millions of travelers each year. From state-of-the-art check-in facilities to expansive, airy concourses, this terminal represents the pinnacle of modern aviation infrastructure. It's a testament to both functional design and environmental responsibility, setting new standards for airports worldwide. Let's take a moment to appreciate the sheer scale and thoughtful integration of its various components, reflecting a harmonious blend of form and function. Now, let's direct our gaze to the right of the main terminal. We come upon Stop Number Two: the vibrant Aeroponic Garden Pod. Look closely at this distinct green, crescent-shaped oasis. This isn't just landscaping; it's a living laboratory! Here, we cultivate fresh produce using aeroponic technology, growing plants without soil and with minimal water. These gardens not only enhance the aesthetic appeal of our terminal but also provide fresh, locally sourced ingredients for the airport's restaurants and cafes, reducing our carbon footprint further. It's an inspiring display of biophilic design, bringing nature into the urban environment and promoting well-being for both passengers and staff. These green spaces are a testament to our dedication to innovation, sustainability, and a holistic approach to airport design. Next, let's look just to the right of the garden. Here we arrive at Stop Number Three: the striking Central Control Tower. This golden, multi-faceted marvel isn't just a visual spectacle; it's the nerve center for all flight operations, orchestrating the ballet of aircraft movements with precision and expertise. Its unique octagonal design, gleaming in the sunlight, symbolizes the advanced technological capabilities housed within, providing unparalleled views of the runways and surrounding airspace. A slender, elegant walkway connects it seamlessly to the main plaza, inviting us closer to admire its intricate details. This tower represents the watchful eye over our skies, ensuring safety and smooth transitions for every departure and arrival. It stands as a powerful symbol of control, innovation, and the future of air traffic management. Continuing our exploration, let's look just above the Central Control Tower. This brings us to Stop Number Four: the mesmerizing Coolant Reservoir. This crescent-shaped body of brilliant blue water is far more than just a decorative feature. It plays a crucial role in our airport's commitment to sustainability, acting as a natural and efficient cooling system for the surrounding facilities. The shimmering blue expanse helps regulate temperatures, reducing our energy footprint and contributing to a healthier environment. It's a prime example of how aesthetic design can merge with practical, eco-conscious engineering. Imagine the peaceful calm it brings to this bustling environment, a serene oasis amidst the dynamic operations of an international airport. Finally, let's broaden our view to the area to the right of the control tower. We are now at Stop Number Five: the grand Arrivals Pavement. This vast, open stone plaza is where stories begin and end, where loved ones reunite, and new adventures commence. It's a meticulously designed pedestrian zone, providing ample space for passengers to navigate comfortably, for vehicles to drop off and pick up, and for everyone to absorb the grandeur of their surroundings. The smooth, light-grey paving complements the modern architecture, guiding visitors effortlessly towards their destinations. This area serves as a welcoming embrace, a transition zone that blends functionality with an open, inviting atmosphere, reflecting the airport's commitment to passenger comfort and convenience. It’s a dynamic space, constantly abuzz with activity, yet designed to feel spacious and intuitive. I hope you've enjoyed this brief but insightful tour of our high-tech international airport terminal. We've witnessed how innovative design, sustainable practices, and thoughtful planning converge to create a truly exceptional travel experience. Thank you for joining me today!",      "labels":[{"number":1,"location_name":"Main Terminal Building A","ymin":80.0,"xmin":80.0,"ymax":920.0,"xmax":540.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The prominent grey architectural structure identified as the primary terminal building, including its integrated glass extensions.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":2,"location_name":"Aeroponic Garden Pod","ymin":288.0,"xmin":550.0,"ymax":400.0,"xmax":630.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"A prominent, distinct green-colored landscaped area forming a specific crescent-shaped garden pod.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":3,"location_name":"Central Control Tower","ymin":434.0,"xmin":566.0,"ymax":852.0,"xmax":852.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The distinct golden octagonal structure and its connecting golden access bridge-like walkway.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":4,"location_name":"Coolant Reservoir","ymin":216.0,"xmin":647.0,"ymax":353.0,"xmax":850.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The distinct blue-colored water feature with a curvilinear shape.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":5,"location_name":"Arrivals Pavement","ymin":400.0,"xmin":852.0,"ymax":800.0,"xmax":920.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The extensive, light-grey paved area facilitating pedestrian circulation and gathering around the central features, distinct from roads.","anchor_policy":"center"}]}
