INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {"script":"Welcome, intrepid explorers, to the marvels of the Ares VI research and colonization facility! I am thrilled to be your guide today as we uncover the ingenuity and dedication that makes life thrive on the red planet. Our journey will take us through the heart of Martian resilience, showcasing the critical infrastructure that sustains our pioneering spirit. As we gather, let's cast our gaze towards the northern perimeter of our compound, where our first significant landmark awaits. \n\nWe begin our exploration by directing our attention to the expansive structure prominently positioned to our north, the **Heavy Equipment Maintenance Bay**. This monumental building, with its distinctive grey roofing, is not just a mere storage facility; it is the bustling nerve center for all large-scale Martian operations. Imagine colossal excavators, sophisticated automated rovers, and vital atmospheric processors being meticulously serviced, repaired, and prepared within these very walls. This bay is where the heavy lifting of terraforming, resource extraction, and large-scale construction is made possible, ensuring that our machinery remains in peak condition to brave the harsh Martian environment. It’s a hive of activity, constantly buzzing with the specialized work vital for our mission’s success and the colony's continuous expansion.\n\nAs we continue our stroll, our path curves gently to the east, bringing into spectacular view the dazzling centerpiece of our colony: the **Central Operations Hub**. With its striking golden, multifaceted dome, this iconic structure isn't just visually stunning; it is the strategic brain of our entire facility. This is where all mission-critical decisions are made, where vast quantities of research data are analyzed, and where our command and control systems meticulously monitor every aspect of colony life, from atmospheric pressure and energy distribution to crew welfare and long-range communications. Its unique hexagonal design is not only architecturally brilliant but also engineered for maximum structural integrity, built to withstand the most formidable Martian dust storms and seismic events. It stands as a radiant beacon of our ambition and technological prowess here on Mars, a true testament to human ingenuity.\n\nFollowing the network of well-defined pathways that fan out from the Central Operations Hub, we now arrive at what we affectionately call the **Arrival and Departure Staging Ground**. This open, stone-paved plaza acts as the primary thoroughfare for all internal and external movements within the facility. Think of it as the main square of our Martian town. It’s a bustling nexus where crews exchange shifts, vital cargo is transferred, and new arrivals first set foot into our thriving community. From here, well-marked pathways lead to every critical sector, making it the perfect vantage point to observe the daily rhythms of colony life and feel the vibrant pulse of our collective endeavor. It truly is the heart of our terrestrial connections, facilitating the constant flow of life and resources.\n\nFrom this central plaza, let’s orient ourselves towards the south-eastern section of our facility. Here, nestled discreetly yet profoundly important, you’ll discover the quiet marvels of the **Atmospheric Algae Cultivation Dome**. Though small in comparison to some of our larger structures, these carefully tended 'green spaces' are incredibly vital to our closed-loop ecosystem. Within their precisely controlled environments, specialized Martian algae are cultivated, playing a dual and indispensable role. Not only do they contribute significantly to oxygen production, constantly purifying the air we breathe, but they also serve as a sustainable source of nutrients for various applications within the colony, including bioplastics and even some supplementary food sources. It's a testament to our commitment to self-sufficiency and ecological balance, proving that even on Mars, life finds a way to flourish and sustain itself.\n\nAnd finally, as we complete our clockwise circuit and move towards the western quadrant of the facility, we encounter the serene and utterly essential **Hydroponic Water Reclamation Pool**. This expansive, shimmering blue reservoir is far more than just a pool; it’s the absolute lifeline of our colony. Here, every precious drop of water – whether from atmospheric condensation, recycled greywater, or extracted subsurface ice – undergoes a rigorous multi-stage purification and recycling process. The purified water then circulates back into our hydroponic farms, crew quarters, and industrial processes, minimizing waste and maximizing efficiency with every cycle. This pool represents the ultimate triumph of sustainable engineering, ensuring that our most precious resource is constantly renewed and conserved, safeguarding the long-term future of our presence on this extraordinary planet. Thank you for joining me on this tour; I hope you’ve gained a deeper appreciation for the wonders of our Martian home!","labels":[{"number":1,"location_name":"Heavy Equipment Maintenance Bay","ymin":85,"xmin":85,"ymax":385,"xmax":540,"semantic_reason":"Visually distinct large grey rectangular building, labeled as 'Grey Roof Heavy Equipment Maintenance Bay'. This is the largest grey structure."},{"number":2,"location_name":"Central Operations Hub","ymin":156,"xmin":450,"ymax":720,"xmax":847,"semantic_reason":"Visually distinct large golden hexagonal building, labeled as 'Central Heagen Operations Hub'. Its unique color and shape make it stand out."},{"number":3,"location_name":"Arrival and Departure Staging Ground","ymin":725,"xmin":430,"ymax":825,"xmax":630,"semantic_reason":"The large central stone pathway intersection and open area south of the golden hub and east of the pool entrance, serving as a primary connection point."},{"number":4,"location_name":"Atmospheric Algae Cultivation Dome","ymin":649,"xmin":860,"ymax":775,"xmax":960,"semantic_reason":"A cluster of three small green trees in the bottom-right fenced area, representing a 'Green Garden' for cultivation."},{"number":5,"location_name":"Hydroponic Water Reclamation Pool","ymin":545,"xmin":165,"ymax":790,"xmax":410,"semantic_reason":"Visually distinct large blue octagonal pool, labeled as 'Hydropaic Zone Water Reliamation Pool'."}]}
