INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {'script': "Welcome, intrepid explorers, to the Triton Deep Sea Research Station! I'm thrilled to be your guide today as we delve into the heart of humanity's most ambitious underwater endeavor. This station is a beacon of innovation, allowing us to study the mysterious abyssal plains and unlock secrets of our planet's last frontier. Prepare to be amazed by the incredible engineering and groundbreaking research happening all around us. We'll be embarking on a walking tour, exploring five critical zones of our facility, starting right here at our command center. Our journey today will take us in a clockwise direction, revealing the interconnected brilliance of Triton. Let's begin!\n\nOur first stop, and indeed the beating heart of our entire operation, is the **Main Operations Module**. As you can see, this sprawling grey complex is a hive of activity. It serves as the primary command and control center for all surface-to-subsurface communications, scientific data processing, and logistical coordination for our deep-sea missions. Imagine countless screens displaying real-time telemetry from submersibles, geological surveys, and bio-acoustic sensors, all managed by our dedicated team of engineers and scientists working tirelessly around the clock. This module is designed for resilience, built to withstand immense pressures and house the cutting-edge technology that makes our deep-sea research possible. It's a true testament to human ingenuity and our relentless pursuit of knowledge.\n\nNow, let's follow the illuminated pathways just to our right, as we make our way to one of the most vital components of the station. Here, glowing with an internal energy that powers our entire facility, is the **Core Energy Reactor**. This golden, hexagonal marvel is where we harness geothermal energy from the ocean floor, converting it into a clean, sustainable power source. Its distinctive glow isn't just for show; it's a visual indicator of the immense energy contained within, constantly fueling our labs, life support systems, and deep-ocean vehicles. Without this incredible piece of technology, sustained habitation and research at these depths would simply be impossible. It’s a testament to our commitment to a self-sufficient and eco-friendly footprint.\n\nContinuing our clockwise journey, let's proceed to the impressive circular structure just ahead of us. Welcome to the **Benthic Specimen Tank**! This enormous, crystal-clear blue pool is home to a meticulously recreated deep-sea ecosystem, housing rare and fascinating organisms brought up from the abyssal depths. Our researchers study these unique creatures in a controlled environment, observing their behaviors, adaptations, and potential for biotechnological advancements. It’s an unparalleled opportunity to witness life forms that thrive under conditions most terrestrial life cannot even comprehend. Take a moment to peer into the simulated depths; you might just catch a glimpse of a newly discovered species!\n\nFrom the chill of the deep-sea tank, let's now make our way around the station to a vibrant, life-sustaining area. On our left, you'll see the lush **Hydroponics Cultivation Dome**. In this self-contained green haven, we cultivate a variety of plants using advanced hydroponic techniques. This 'green garden' provides a crucial source of fresh produce for our crew, significantly reducing our reliance on resupply missions from the surface. It’s a closed-loop system, efficiently recycling water and nutrients, showcasing sustainable living in one of the most extreme environments on Earth. It reminds us that even at the bottom of the ocean, life finds a way to flourish.\n\nFinally, let's complete our loop around the station as we arrive at our last, but certainly not least, destination: the **Submersible Deployment Platform**. This robust, grey platform serves as the crucial staging and launch area for our fleet of advanced research submersibles. From here, remotely operated vehicles (ROVs) and human-occupied vehicles (HOVs) are prepared, deployed, and recovered after their daring expeditions into the deep. This platform is the gateway to our direct interaction with the ocean floor, enabling us to collect samples, conduct surveys, and explore hydrothermal vents. It’s where the thrill of discovery truly begins!\n\nThank you for joining me on this tour of the Triton Deep Sea Research Station. I hope you've gained a deeper appreciation for the incredible work being done here to expand our understanding of the ocean's profound mysteries. Feel free to ask any questions you may have as we conclude our extraordinary journey!", 'labels': [{'number': 1, 'location_name': 'Main Operations Module', 'ymin': 22.0, 'xmin': 15.0, 'ymax': 710.0, 'xmax': 480.0, 'x': 247.5, 'y': 366.0, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'The largest, most complex grey structure, representing the central command and control hub of the facility.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 2, 'location_name': 'Core Energy Reactor', 'ymin': 155.0, 'xmin': 540.0, 'ymax': 395.0, 'xmax': 780.0, 'x': 660.0, 'y': 275.0, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'A prominent golden hexagonal module, visually distinct and suggestive of a powerful energy source.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 3, 'location_name': 'Benthic Specimen Tank', 'ymin': 435.0, 'xmin': 440.0, 'ymax': 795.0, 'xmax': 805.0, 'x': 622.5, 'y': 615.0, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'A large, circular, blue body of water, clearly indicating an aquatic containment or research tank.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 4, 'location_name': 'Hydroponics Cultivation Dome', 'ymin': 795.0, 'xmin': 135.0, 'ymax': 885.0, 'xmax': 345.0, 'x': 240.0, 'y': 840.0, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'A distinct green, rectangular area connected to the main complex, visually resembling an agricultural or cultivation zone.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}, {'number': 5, 'location_name': 'Submersible Deployment Platform', 'ymin': 708.0, 'xmin': 199.0, 'ymax': 768.0, 'xmax': 341.0, 'x': 270.0, 'y': 738.0, 'bbox_type': 'landmark', 'semantic_reason': 'A distinct, flat, grey rectangular platform-like structure connecting main complex to the cultivation dome, suitable for vehicle or equipment staging.', 'anchor_policy': 'center'}]}
