INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {"script":"Welcome, dear adventurers, to a truly remarkable example of modern healthcare architecture, our esteemed City Hospital Wing! I'm absolutely delighted to be your guide today as we explore the innovative design and functional beauty of this campus. We'll begin our journey at the very heart of arrival and transition, the magnificent Main Entrance Plaza.\n\nImagine yourselves just having arrived, perhaps by car or on foot, taking in the serene and open atmosphere of this grand Main Entrance Plaza. This spacious, welcoming area is designed to provide a sense of calm and clarity from the moment you step onto our grounds. The sweeping stone pathways guide you effortlessly towards the main building, offering ample space for arrival and reflection. Notice the elegant circular feature in the plaza, a subtle nod to both aesthetic beauty and functional design, helping to orient visitors and create a focal point of arrival before you even step inside. It's the perfect prelude to the world-class care housed within.\n\nNow, as we proceed forward, just beyond the plaza, we find ourselves standing before the impressive Central Surgical Block. This is the very core of our hospital's clinical operations, a testament to cutting-edge medical science and architectural precision. This expansive, multi-story structure is where life-saving procedures are performed daily. Its robust design houses numerous operating theaters, recovery suites, and critical care units, all meticulously planned for efficiency and patient comfort. You can truly appreciate the thoughtful planning that went into creating a facility of this scale, ensuring seamless operations while providing a nurturing environment for both patients and staff.\n\nFrom here, let's take a moment to peek into what we lovingly refer to as our Therapeutic Garden Courtyard. Tucked away within the heart of the Central Surgical Block, this serene, enclosed space offers a vital sanctuary. Though we can only glimpse it from certain vantage points or specific corridors, it's designed as an oasis of tranquility. Its purpose is to provide a restorative natural environment, offering a quiet escape and a visual respite for patients, families, and our dedicated medical teams. The concept here is that healing extends beyond clinical treatment, embracing the psychological and emotional well-being that connection with nature provides, even in a bustling hospital setting.\n\nContinuing our journey, we now turn our attention to one of the most visually striking elements of our campus: the Diagnostic Imaging Wing. You can't miss its magnificent golden, multi-faceted dome, a true architectural jewel! This unique octagonal structure is not just beautiful; it symbolizes the advanced technology housed within. It's here that our expert teams utilize state-of-the-art MRI, CT, and other imaging modalities to provide crucial diagnostic information, guiding treatment plans with unparalleled precision. The wing's distinctive shape was purposefully chosen to maximize natural light where appropriate and create an uplifting, modern environment for patients undergoing critical diagnostic tests.\n\nFinally, as we complete our loop, we arrive at the large, tranquil HVAC Cooling Pond, located right next to the Diagnostic Imaging Wing. Far from being merely utilitarian, this substantial body of water plays a crucial environmental role in our campus. It's an integral part of our sustainable infrastructure, efficiently managing the cooling systems for the entire hospital complex. But beyond its engineering function, notice how it also contributes significantly to the aesthetics of the hospital grounds. The gentle ripples, and the subtle aeration features you see, create a calming auditory and visual experience, offering a sense of peace and contributing to the overall healing atmosphere of our remarkable hospital wing. Thank you for joining me on this tour; I hope you've gained a deeper appreciation for the thoughtful design and dedication that makes this facility truly exceptional.","labels":[{"number":1,"location_name":"Main Entrance Plaza","ymin":750.0,"xmin":120.0,"ymax":950.0,"xmax":320.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The large open white area at the bottom-left of the complex, indicating a primary entry point or communal gathering space, including a circular design element.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":2,"location_name":"Central Surgical Block","ymin":0.0,"xmin":0.0,"ymax":749.0,"xmax":670.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The dominant, large L-shaped grey building that forms the main structure of the hospital.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":3,"location_name":"Therapeutic Garden Courtyard","ymin":580.0,"xmin":245.0,"ymax":670.0,"xmax":335.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"A distinct, enclosed white rectangular space located within the main grey building, visually suitable for a courtyard or garden area.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":4,"location_name":"Diagnostic Imaging Wing","ymin":235.0,"xmin":505.0,"ymax":685.0,"xmax":875.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The prominent, multi-faceted golden octagonal structure labeled 'Diagnostic Imaging Wing' on the map.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":5,"location_name":"HVAC Cooling Pond","ymin":650.0,"xmin":540.0,"ymax":980.0,"xmax":980.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The large, rectangular blue body of water with three visible fountains, labeled 'HVAC Zone Cooling Pond' on the map.","anchor_policy":"center"}]}
