INFO:tools.adk_tools:Content of vision_proposal: {"script":"Welcome, adventurers, to the cutting-edge marvel that is our High-Tech International Airport Terminal! I'm thrilled to be your guide today as we embark on an exclusive aerial tour of this breathtaking facility. Prepare to be amazed by the seamless integration of technology, sustainability, and human-centric design. We'll explore five key areas that make this terminal a global leader. Let's begin our journey right here, overlooking what we call the Terminal A Main Concourse Roof. This isn't just any rooftop; it's a vibrant, active space designed for efficiency and guest comfort. Notice the lush green installations and subtle architectural elements that cleverly disguise vital infrastructure. This area, while looking like a serene green space, is actually a crucial access point and a testament to our commitment to blending natural beauty with advanced urban planning. It's often the first glimpse many travelers have of our innovative design, setting the tone for their entire journey. From here, passengers can access various amenities and enjoy a unique perspective of the surrounding cityscape before or after their flights. It’s a dynamic hub, constantly buzzing with activity, yet designed to feel open and calming. As we continue our clockwise progression, our next stop brings us to the very heart of the terminal's operational intelligence: the magnificent Central Data Nexus Hub. Just gaze upon that stunning, multi-faceted golden hexagonal structure! It’s not just a striking piece of architecture; it's the brain of our entire operation. This colossal hub processes an unimaginable amount of data every second, coordinating everything from flight schedules and baggage handling to energy distribution and passenger flow. Its intricate design symbolizes the complex, interconnected systems that ensure every aspect of your travel experience is optimized for speed, safety, and comfort. It’s a true icon of modern engineering and digital prowess, visible from many points across the terminal, a beacon of our commitment to innovation. Now, let's zoom in a little closer, right into the vibrant blue core of that golden hexagon. This mesmerizing blue glow signifies our next point of interest, the Coolant Recirculation Basin. This critical system is more than just a beautiful light show; it's the lifeblood of the Central Data Nexus Hub. The intense data processing within the hub generates significant heat, and this advanced basin continuously circulates specialized coolants to maintain optimal operating temperatures. It’s a closed-loop, highly efficient system that exemplifies our dedication to sustainable practices, ensuring the longevity and reliability of our most vital technological assets while minimizing environmental impact. It’s a quiet hero, diligently working behind the scenes to keep our high-tech operations running smoothly, 24/7. Continuing our circular journey, let’s shift our gaze to the opposite side of the main terminal building, where you'll discover another marvel of eco-conscious design: the Vertical Aeroponic Garden. Just like the green spaces we saw on the other side of the roof, these vibrant green installations are not merely decorative. This is a state-of-the-art aeroponic farm, growing fresh produce that’s used right here in the terminal’s restaurants and cafes. Imagine enjoying a meal, knowing that the ingredients were harvested just hours ago, right above your head! These gardens contribute to the terminal's air quality, reduce our carbon footprint, and provide a calming, natural aesthetic amidst the technological sophistication. They are a living testament to our commitment to health, sustainability, and providing a fresh, local experience for our travelers. Finally, as we complete our immersive tour, we arrive at the expansive area stretching out beneath the main structure, which we proudly call the Arrivals Processing Plaza. This vast, open space is the first point of contact for countless international visitors, and it's designed for both grandeur and efficiency. Here, state-of-the-art biometric scanners and intelligent flow systems guide passengers smoothly from their aircraft to ground transportation, minimizing wait times and enhancing the arrival experience. Its minimalist design and clear pathways are intentional, ensuring a stress-free transition into the city. It’s not just a plaza; it’s a gateway, meticulously engineered to handle high volumes of traffic while maintaining a welcoming and intuitive environment. This plaza truly embodies the modern travel experience – fast, efficient, and forward-thinking. Thank you for joining me on this fascinating aerial tour of our High-Tech International Airport Terminal. We hope you've gained a deeper appreciation for the innovation, sustainability, and thoughtful design that makes this facility a landmark in global aviation. Safe travels, and we look forward to welcoming you back soon!","labels":[{"number":1,"location_name":"Terminal A Main Concourse Roof","ymin":0.0,"xmin":0.0,"ymax":221.0,"xmax":215.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"Visible green areas and structures on the rooftop, indicating an amenity or entrance point.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":2,"location_name":"Central Data Nexus Hub","ymin":341.0,"xmin":373.0,"ymax":659.0,"xmax":627.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The prominent, visually distinct golden hexagonal structure at the center.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":3,"location_name":"Coolant Recirculation Basin","ymin":400.0,"xmin":400.0,"ymax":400.0,"xmax":400.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"The glowing blue internal components within the golden hexagonal structure.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":4,"location_name":"Vertical Aeroponic Garden","ymin":765.0,"xmin":0.0,"ymax":988.0,"xmax":180.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"Green landscaped areas on the rooftop section, symmetrical to the initial point.","anchor_policy":"center"},{"number":5,"location_name":"Arrivals Processing Plaza","ymin":757.0,"xmin":0.0,"ymax":1000.0,"xmax":1000.0,"x":null,"y":null,"bbox_type":"landmark","semantic_reason":"Large, open, dark grey paved area at the base of the terminal structure, suitable for processing arrivals.","anchor_policy":"center"}]}
